It&rsquo;s never over until the fat lady sings, but I do believe I heard a buxom lass clearing her throat this afternoon in a preparatory sort of way. After entering our 10th&nbsp;and final state this morning, we had another day of reasonably stiff climbing. James&rsquo; thigh is definitely on the mend and we averaged 14.5 mph over the 78 mile ride. This leaves just 60 miles tomorrow until we dip our front wheel in the Atlantic.






James and Chris were delighted with the sunny welcome to New Hampshire



