Today&rsquo;s ride was pleasant and fast. Good roads, a slight tail wind and not too many hills. So we rattled along at 18.4 mph. But James is developing a slightly worrying pain in his left thigh. He spent the final 2 hours of the ride calling a score between 6 and 8 on the Pain Register, interspersed with the sort of swearing you&rsquo;d expect from a bunch of sailors not an aspiring academic.
