Take a medium sized stoker.
Remove all excess fat. This can be a lengthy and tedious process but it is well worth the effort. It is, however, worth leaving the small fatty deposits at the junction of the haunches as stripping these right back can release bile that may ruin the subsequent meal entirely.
Tenderize the rump well. One recommended implement for this step is the Brooks Saddle - see the Heggie description here, starting at around 4:50.
Stuff the stoker with as much banana and raisins as possible and moisturise well with Gatorade (most of this will evaporate over the next 4 hours, so make sure to keep topping up).
Glaze liberally with suncream.
Bake for 4 hours under a moderate sun in a fan assisted, constant pressure paceline (the Davey Train works particularly well).
