Today was a Flatterday Saturday. Although we had headwinds again (!) they were nowhere near as soul destroying as yesterday, and we managed to hook on to the Davey Train once more, so knocked out the 70 miles at 17.4 mph to be at Brantford by 12.15 in time for a relaxed lunch with adult beverage on the hotel terrace.&nbsp;
On extended trips like this one there are many opportunities for people to describe scenery to me. This proves to be an incredibly difficult thing to do. It&rsquo;s relatively straightforward to describe what the scenery actually is, but much harder to describe why it is beautiful or to differentiate it from other&nbsp;notionally&nbsp;similar scenery.
