After a slight diversion due to construction work, today just tipped over into being our second consecutive century. But with relentless headwinds, many miles of bone rattling road surfaces and what felt like much more than 2,050 ft of climbing, it certainly felt like a tough one.






Photo courtesy&nbsp;of Martin Stabler



For the past 3 days we have been travelling through industrial scale livestock farming country, so there is very little visual to report. I am actually on an equal footing to everyone else regarding the major sensory input in these parts. Unpleasantly, that&rsquo;s because the most noticeable thing around here is the smell of the Swine Express trucks and the processing plants they are supplying. Not nice.
Factoid: One of the&nbsp;a meat processing plants we passed in Worthington "harvests" 25,000 hogs a day...
